6
0:00:28.26,000 --> 0:00:31,000
where fun is serious business.

7
0:00:31.26,000 --> 0:00:33,000
And no, this isn't Burning Man

8
0:00:33.26,000 --> 0:00:35,000
or San Francisco.

9
0:00:35.26,000 --> 0:00:37,000
(Laughter)

10
0:00:37.26,000 --> 0:00:4,000
Ladies and gentlemen, meet your cousins.

11
0:00:40.26,000 --> 0:00:43,000
This is the world of wild bonobos

12
0:00:43.26,000 --> 0:00:45,000
in the jungles of Congo.

13
0:00:45.26,000 --> 0:00:48,000
Bonobos are, together with chimpanzees,

14
0:00:48.26,000 --> 0:00:51,000
your living closest relative.

15
0:00:51.26,000 --> 0:00:54,000
That means we all share a common ancestor,

16
0:00:54.26,000 --> 0:00:56,000
an evolutionary grandmother,

17
0:00:56.26,000 --> 0:00:59,000
who lived around six million years ago.

18
0:01:00.26,000 --> 0:01:02,000
Now, chimpanzees are well-known

19
0:01:02.26,000 --> 0:01:04,000
for their aggression.

20
0:01:04.26,000 --> 0:01:07,000
(Laughter)

21
0:01:07.26,000 --> 0:01:09,000
But unfortunately,

22
0:01:09.26,000 --> 0:01:11,000
we have made too much of an emphasis

23
0:01:11.26,000 --> 0:01:13,000
of this aspect

24
0:01:13.26,000 --> 0:01:16,000
in our narratives of human evolution.

25
0:01:16.26,000 --> 0:01:18,000
But bonobos show us

26
0:01:18.26,000 --> 0:01:2,000
the other side of the coin.

27
0:01:20.26,000 --> 0:01:22,000
While chimpanzees

28
0:01:22.26,000 --> 0:01:25,000
are dominated by big, scary guys,

29
0:01:25.26,000 --> 0:01:27,000
bonobo society

30
0:01:27.26,000 --> 0:01:3,000
is run by empowered females.

31
0:01:31.26,000 --> 0:01:34,000
These guys have really worked something out,

32
0:01:34.26,000 --> 0:01:37,000
since this leads to a highly tolerant society

33
0:01:37.26,000 --> 0:01:39,000
where fatal violence

34
0:01:39.26,000 --> 0:01:42,000
has not been observed yet.

35
0:01:42.26,000 --> 0:01:44,000
But unfortunately,

36
0:01:44.26,000 --> 0:01:46,000
bonobos are the least understood

37
0:01:46.26,000 --> 0:01:48,000
of the great apes.

38
0:01:48.26,000 --> 0:01:51,000
They live in the depths of the Congolese jungle,

39
0:01:51.26,000 --> 0:01:54,000
and it has been very difficult to study them.

40
0:01:54.26,000 --> 0:01:57,000
The Congo is a paradox --

41
0:01:57.26,000 --> 0:02:01,000
a land of extraordinary biodiversity and beauty,

42
0:02:01.26,000 --> 0:02:04,000
but also the heart of darkness itself --

43
0:02:04.26,000 --> 0:02:07,000
the scene of a violent conflict

44
0:02:07.26,000 --> 0:02:09,000
that has raged for decades

45
0:02:09.26,000 --> 0:02:12,000
and claimed nearly as many lives

46
0:02:12.26,000 --> 0:02:15,000
as the First World War.

47
0:02:16.26,000 --> 0:02:18,000
